    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This ring buffer handles incoming spikes. It spans an interval equal to the longest arrival delay. When a spike event is notified it puts it into the slot defined by the arrival time. It just adds the weight onto the existing value in this slot, assuming a linear summation of the weights of coincident inputs. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
